Beegalu J.

 CI/CD ‚Äî What‚Äôs Actually Happening Behind the Scenes?

> When I first heard about CI/CD, I honestly thought it was just some fancy automation buzzword.

But after playing around with Jenkins and GitHub, I finally get it.

Here‚Äôs what really happens when you push your code üëá

üß© Continuous Integration (CI):
Every time you commit code, Jenkins (or GitHub Actions) jumps in builds your project, runs tests, and checks if you accidentally broke something. Basically, your friendly robot tester ü§ñ

üöÄ Continuous Deployment (CD):
Once everything passes, it automatically sends your updated code straight to the server (like AWS EC2 or Kubernetes). No manual steps. No ‚Äúworks on my machine‚Äù drama.

In short:
CI/CD = Code goes from laptop ‚Üí production ‚Üí live ‚Äî automatically.

That‚Äôs the real DevOps magic ‚ú®**
