I Recently Had a DevOps / Cloud Engineer Interview ‚Äì Sharing My Questions
I had a technical interview recently for a DevOps / Cloud Engineer position.
 I‚Äôm sharing the list of questions that were asked ‚Äî this might help anyone who is preparing for similar roles in DevOps, Cloud, or SRE.
üí¨ Interview Questions:
1Ô∏è‚É£ About You and Your Work:
Can you give a short introduction about yourself and your experience?
2Ô∏è‚É£ Terraform and Ansible:
How have you used Terraform and Ansible? Can you give an example of what you built using them?
How did you reuse the same Terraform code for different environments?
How did you manage and use secrets securely when connecting to AWS or Azure?
3Ô∏è‚É£ Working with Teams and Standards:
How did you gather requirements before writing Terraform code? Did you work with other teams?
How do you handle disagreements with teams about cloud resources or setups?
How do you make sure everyone follows standards while still meeting team needs?
4Ô∏è‚É£ Code Reviews and Pipelines:
How do you make sure Terraform code is reviewed and consistent before deployment?
How did you set up Terraform reviews and deployments in GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps, or Jenkins?
How did you manage Terraform deployments for multiple environments?
What other CI/CD pipelines have you built? Can you explain your complete CD process?
5Ô∏è‚É£ Kubernetes and CI/CD:
Can you explain the CI/CD flow you used to deploy apps on Kubernetes?
What security tools or scans did you use in your pipelines?
6Ô∏è‚É£ Automation and Scripting:
Can you give an example of using PowerShell for cost optimization or automation?
Was your PowerShell automation part of CI or CD?
7Ô∏è‚É£ Monitoring and Infrastructure:
How would you set up monitoring for Kubernetes or applications using Grafana and Prometheus?
How would you use Terraform to create cloud resources?
How would you configure an Ansible agent?
How would you create IAM roles in Terraform? Did you use any modules or templates?
Have you built Docker containers? What were they used for and how did you do it?
It was a great interview that covered a lot of real-world DevOps topics like Infrastructure as Code (IaC), CI/CD, automation, security, and monitoring.
 Hope this helps others who are preparing ‚Äî reviewing these topics can really boost your confidence!
