Muhammad Ilya
Commonly asked questions on Terraform in an Interview

üß© 1Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Terraform State File?
The terraform.tfstate file is the source of truth for your infrastructure.
 It maps your Terraform configuration to real-world resources.
üí° Tip: Store it remotely (S3, Azure Blob, Terraform Cloud) for team collaboration and state locking.

üîí 2Ô∏è‚É£ What Happens If You Lose the State File?
Terraform forgets what‚Äôs deployed ‚Äî it might try to recreate everything 
‚úÖ Always enable remote backends + versioning to recover easily.

‚öôÔ∏è 3Ô∏è‚É£ What is Terraform Drift?
Drift happens when the actual infrastructure differs from what‚Äôs defined in your Terraform code.
Example: Someone modifies an EC2 instance directly in AWS Console.
üí¨ Command to detect: terraform plan

üîÅ 4Ô∏è‚É£ How Do You Fix Drift?
You can either:
* Update your Terraform configuration to match actual changes, or
* Run terraform apply to restore the desired state.

üåç 5Ô∏è‚É£ How to Handle Multiple Environments (Dev, Stage, Prod)?
Use Workspaces or separate state files/backends for each environment.
 This keeps your infra isolated, safe, and easier to manage.
